    "CO gas monitoring and control systems",
    "UniCo is a sensor designed for measuring the level of toxic gases of the oxygen type\nMonocarbon CO which is a byproduct of the operation of gasoline engines in parking lots.\nThe feeling has excellent stability, including a low level of reaction to changes in temperature\nand other gases found in the parking lot.\nThe emotion is fed from a low voltage 24VAC, and is connected by communication to a floor controller whose role is\nUse the information coming from floor sensors and operate the ventilation system accordingly.\nThe advantage of using emotion with communication is expressed in significant financial savings - savings in wiring and this compared to other emotions that require direct wiring from the emotion to the controller.\n​\nCO Controller\n​\nSupeBrain CO controller - is an independent controller that can be programmed and includes an internal clock that allows the blowers to be activated according to a weekly time schedule and changes in the CO level.\nThe controller includes 2 communication ports, one RS485 for communication with the CO sensors and TCP/IP for communication with the central control computer.",
    "Related Products",
    "Control Applications Ltd",
    "making contact\nPhone: +972-3-6474998\n​\nFax: +972-3-6474598\nEmail:\ncal@ddc.co.il",
    "opening hours\nControl Applications Ltd\nSunday - Thursday\n08:00 - 17:00",
    "Address\n25 Barzel Street, Tel Aviv\n6971035\nIsrael",
